author: AceShowbiz.com
title: Selena Gomez's 'Revival' Debuts Atop Billboard 200
text:
Comments The first of The Game's two-part release of 'The Documentary 2' and Jana Kramer's 'Thirty One' are the only other newcomers in the chart's top 10. 
Selena Gomez 's " Revival " is officially topping Billboard 200. The album, marking the former Disney star's first to arrive under Interscope, debuts at the list's No. 1 with 117,000 equivalent album units collected in the week ending on October 15, according to Nielsen Music. With 85,000 in pure album sales, the album posts Gomez's second best sales week yet, following its predecessor " Stars Dance " that gave the 23-year-old singer her first No. 1 effort on the chart with 97,000 back in 2013. Trailing behind "Revival" at Billboard 200's No. 2 is the first of a two-part release of The Game 's " The Documentary 2 ". It opens with 95,000 units including 83,000 in album sales. The second part of the sequel to 2005's " The Documentary " came out last Friday. A bunch of familiar titles dominate the rest of this week's top 10. The Weeknd 's " Beauty Behind the Madness " falls one rung to No. 3 with 77,000 and Fetty Wap 's self-titled debut set stays at No. 4 with 53,000. Drake and Future 's " What a Time to Be Alive " rounds out the top 5 with 49,000. Taylor Swift is sitting at No. 6 with another 37,000. While Luke Bryan 's " Kill the Lights " rises from No. 9 to No. 7 with 31,000, Janet Jackson 's " Unbreakable " which last week arrived at No. 1 plunges to this week's No. 8 with 30,000 in its second week. Thomas Rhett 's " Tangled Up " is at No. 9 with 27.000. The third and last newcomer in the top 10 is Jana Kramer 's " Thirty One ". It starts with 22,000 units.
